cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MA 

This paper deals with congestion control in vehicular networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses optimization techniques to control the beaconing rate, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
